# Doc Style

> **Template**: Copy to `.cursor/rules/doc-style.mdc`
> These rules apply when AI generates or edits documentation.

---

## Three Rules

1. **Value only** - Include only information that helps someone
2. **Mermaid for diagrams** - Visual > text for complex flows
3. **Structure over prose** - Tables and bullets, not paragraphs

---

## Value Only

Ask: "Does this help someone do something?"

| Include | Skip |
|---------|------|
| How to do X | History of X |
| What to avoid | Obvious statements |
| Quick reference | Verbose explanations |

```markdown
# Good: Actionable
Run `npm install` then `npm run dev`

# Bad: No value added
This project uses npm for package management.
```

---

## Diagrams vs Tables

| Context | Use |
|---------|-----|
| **AI-read files** (AGENTS.md, .mdc rules) | Tables - fewer tokens, AI parses text not visuals |
| **Human-read docs** (READMEs, guides) | Mermaid - visual clarity for complex flows |

### When to Use Mermaid

- Workflows with 4+ steps
- Architecture with multiple components
- Sequence diagrams (interactions)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Spec --> Build --> Review --> Deploy
```

### When to Use Tables

- Simple relationships (A references B)
- Lists of items with attributes
- AGENTS.md Context Loading section

